  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Platform Lead - Trading",
  "description": "<p><strong>Why explore</strong></p><ul><li>An opportunity to drive improvements</li><li>Exposure to global operations, processes and stakeholders</li><li>Work in a collaborative and fast paced environment</li><li>Based in Singapore, a global commercial hub for Rio Tinto</li></ul><p><strong>About the role</strong><br />We are seeking a highly skilled and proactive <strong>Platform Lead</strong> to join our Digital Division. In this pivotal role, you will lead platform support team, coaching analysts/developers, and ensuring smooth integration with business-as-usual operations.<br /><br />Reporting to the Platform Manager, you will:</p><ul><li>Oversee product/platform governance, ensuring applications meet scalability, security, and business objectives.</li><li>Guide platform analysts and developers to deliver reliable, high-value digital solutions.</li><li>Maintain technical integrity and performance through standards and best practices.</li><li>Manage operational risks and ensure timely resolution of platform-related issues.</li><li>Align resource allocation and budgeting with delivery objective.</li><li>Ensure compliance with governance frameworks and vendor management.</li><li>Support career development and knowledge-sharing initiatives.</li><li>Provide strategic direction for platform management aligned with digital division goals.</li><li>Drive initiatives that enhance platform capabilities and support organizational objectives.</li><li>Promote collaboration among business stakeholders, analysts, developers, and project teams to deliver seamless project implementation and business continuity.</li></ul><p><strong>Domain Knowledge Required:</strong></p><ul><li>Deep understanding in derivative trading, physical commodity trading including MtM and accounting posting.</li><li>Experienced in various integration pattern between CTRM to ERP and/or other digital platforms. </li><li>Familiarity with CTRM/ETRM systems; Fusion by Fendahl is preferred.</li><li>Knowledge of ZE by ZEMA is preferred.</li></ul><p><strong>About you</strong><br /><strong>To be successfully considered for this role, you will have:</strong></p><ul><li>Relevant degree qualifications.</li><li>10+ years in application development and delivery, including 5–7 years in managerial roles.</li><li>Proven leadership and stakeholder management experience, guiding system/platform teams.</li><li>Solid knowledge of SDLC, data governance, release management, and IT risk/compliance.</li><li>Strong understanding of project management, change control, risk management, and awareness of emerging technology trends.</li><li>Experience with platform governance, operational risk management, and vendor management.</li></ul>",
